article.description: Paulius Satkus scored a career-high 22 points and James Madison won for the first time at home this season with an 82-65 victory over Division III Eastern Mennonite on Wednesday night.
article.headline: James Madison beats Eastern Mennonite to snap 4-game skid
article.linkText: James Madison beats Eastern Mennonite to snap 4-game skid
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Paulius Satkus scored a career-high 22 points and James Madison won for the first time at home this season with an 82-65 victory over Division III Eastern Mennonite on Wednesday night. Satkus was 9 of 12 from the field. Jackson Kent added 17 points on 6-of-12 shooting for James Madison (2-11), which shot 54 percent from the floor. Ramone Snowden had 12 points and Ivan Lukic chipped in 10 points for the Dukes. Joey McLean added eight points and a game-high five assists. Isaiah Harris-Winn and Jerome Jones scored 16 points apiece to lead Eastern Mennonite. The game was tied 37-37 at halftime. The Dukes used a 20-10 run and led 63-52 midway through the second half and cruised from there. James Madison snapped a four-game skid and bounced back from a one-point loss at home to UMBC on Friday.
